er, tissue rOEF during exercise in subjects with FM was significantly lower than in healthy controls, and the half-times of oxygenation recovery ($\Delta$[HbO2] and $\Delta$[Hb]) were significantly longer following fatiguing exercise and cuff occlusion.Conclusions: Our results suggest an alteration of muscle oxygen utilization in the FM population. This study demonstrates the potential of using combined diffuse optical spectroscopies (i.e., NIRS/DCS) to comprehensively evaluate tissue oxygen and flow kinetics in skeletal muscle. {\textcopyright} 2012 Shang et al.; licensee BioMed Central Ltd.},
author = {Shang, Yu and Gurley, Katelyn and Symons, Brock and Long, Douglas and Srikuea, Ratchakrit and Crofford, Leslie J. and Peterson, Charlotte A. and Yu, Guoqiang},
